******
[3] Ohio
Date: Wed 24 Oct 2018
Source: Daily Jeffersonian [edited]
https://www.daily-jeff.com/news/20181024/hepatitis-cases-continue-to-rise


The Ohio Department of Health declared a statewide outbreak of hepatitis A in June 2018, and the cases are continuing to rise. As of 22 Oct 2018, Ohio has reported 717 cases affecting 54 counties, including Noble, Guernsey, Monroe and Washington counties. In 2017, Ohio recorded only 45 cases for the year.

Outbreaks of hepatitis A are occurring in several states across the USA, including neighboring states of Indiana, Kentucky, Michigan and West Virginia.

